data: {"type":"local_debate","debate":{"agreement":"unanimous","method":"consensus-vote","confidence":0.97,"winnerId":"answer-engine","winnerLabel":"Crucible Answer Engine","contributors":["answer-engine","gemma2-2b","track-s-fm"],"mindsChanged":false,"totalLatencyMs":33744,"rounds":[{"kind":"propose","entries":[{"modelId":"answer-engine","modelLabel":"Crucible Answer Engine","text":"```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"title\": \"IPv4 Address Validation\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"ip\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"pattern\": \"^((25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|1[0-9]{2}|[1-9]?[0-9])\\.){3}(25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|1[0-9]{2}|[1-9]?[0-9])$\",\n      \"description\": \"A valid IPv4 address\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\"ip\"]\n}\n```","latencyMs":0,"errored":false,"changedPosition":false},{"modelId":"gemma2-2b","modelLabel":"Gemma 2 2B Instruct","text":"```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"string\",\n  \"description\": \"A valid IPv4 address.\",\n  \"pattern\": \"^(([0-9]|[1-9][0-9]|1[0-9]{2}|2[0-4][0-9]|25[0-5])\\\\.){3}([0-9]|[1-2][0-9]|3[0-2])$\", \n}\n\n```\n\n\n**Explanation:**\n\n* **`type: string`**: This specifies that the schema expects a value of type `string`.\n* **`description:`**: A brief description for human readability, explaining what this field represents (a valid IPv4 address).\n* **`pattern:`**:  This is where we define the regular expression to validate the input against. Let's break down its components:\n\n    * **`^(([0-9]|\\d{1,2}|1\\d{2}|\\d{3})\\\\.)+([0-9]|1[2]…","latencyMs":33742,"errored":false,"changedPosition":false},{"modelId":"track-s-fm","modelLabel":"Apple On-Device (Track S)","text":"```json\n{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"title\": \"IPv4 Address Validation\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"address\": {\n      \"type\": \"string\",\n      \"pattern\": \"^((25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|1[0-9]{2}|[1-9]?[0-9])\\.){3}(25[0-5]|2[0-4][0-9]|1[0-9]{2}|[1-9]?[0-9])$\",\n      \"description\": \"A valid IPv4 address must consist of four octets separated by dots, with each octet ranging from 0 to 255.\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"required\": [\"address\"],\n  \"additionalProperties\": false\n}\n```","latencyMs":4677,"errored":false,"changedPosition":false}]}]}}

